The archives of the Edinburgh Royal Choral Union contain rolls of
		  members since 1866 and including lists of patrons, officers, and directors;
		  correspondence for the period 1877-83; correspondence with members, 1957-69;
		  correspondence with choirs, 1857-1979; minute books from 1881; accounts ledger
		  1960-75; programmes from the 1940s onwards; bulletins and news-sheets for the
		  National Federation of Musical Societies; press cuttings book; receipts;
		  accounts; posters; and, the ERCU seal with its embossing machine.
